  <mads:note type="source">"Ae'schrion an iambic poet, a native of Samos...." Smith's Dictionary of
      Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 1, 1867, p. 40.</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">"Aeschrion The Suda (s. v. 354 Adler) mentions an epic writer from
      Mytilene, companion of Alexander the Great and pupil of Aristotle (no quotations extant); Ath.
      7,296f and 8,335c-d quotes choliambic verses of an A. of Samos. Tzetz. Chil. 8,398 ff. names
      -- perhaps rightly so -- only A. of Mytilene, an author of both genres." Robbins, Emmet
      (Toronto). "Aeschrion." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and
      Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2007. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 17 July 2007</mads:note>
